Excellent! Now let me compile comprehensive best practices and patterns.

## Complete GitHub Search Results: Documentation Layouts with Side Navigation

Based on my search of production React/Next.js codebases, here are the **best code patterns** for documentation/article layouts with sidebars and table of contents:

---

## 1. SIDEBAR SECTION NAVIGATION PATTERNS

### Pattern A: Sticky Sidebar with Fixed Header Offset
**From:** Vercel Workflow, AsyncAPI, GitHub Docs

```typescript
// Layout structure
<div className="grid md:grid-cols-[286px_1fr_286px]">
  {/* Sticky left sidebar */}
  <div className="md:sticky md:top-16 md:max-h-[calc(100vh-4rem)] md:overflow-y-auto">
    {/* Navigation content */}
  </div>

  {/* Main content */}
  <div className="prose flex-1">
    {/* Article content */}
  </div>

  {/* Optional sticky right sidebar for table of contents */}
  <div className="md:sticky md:top-16 md:max-h-[calc(100vh-4rem)] md:overflow-y-auto">
    {/* TOC navigation */}
  </div>
</div>
```

**Key Tailwind Classes:**
- `md:sticky` - Position sticky on medium+ screens
- `md:top-16` - Offset from header (adjust for your header height)
- `md:max-h-[calc(100vh-4rem)]` - Prevent sidebar overflow
- `md:overflow-y-auto` - Allow vertical scrolling within sidebar

### Pattern B: Mobile-First Responsive
**From:** Supabase, AsyncAPI

```typescript
// Hidden on mobile, visible on large screens
<aside className="hidden lg:flex lg:shrink-0">
  <div className="flex w-64 flex-col border-r border-gray-200 bg-white py-2">
    <div className="flex flex-1 flex-col md:sticky md:top-20 md:max-h-(screen-14) md:overflow-y-auto">
      <nav className="flex-1">{navigation}</nav>
    </div>
  </div>
</aside>
```

---

## 2. ACTIVE SECTION HIGHLIGHTING PATTERNS

### Pattern A: IntersectionObserver with Root Margin
**From:** Flowbite React (Most Robust)

```typescript
export function TableOfContents() {
  const [activeId, setActiveId] = useState<string>();

  useEffect(() => {
    // Create observer with aggressive root margin
    const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
      (entries) => {
        // Sort by position to get topmost visible heading
        const visibleEntries = entries
          .filter((entry) => entry.isIntersecting)
          .sort((a, b) => {
            const aRect = a.target.getBoundingClientRect();
            const bRect = b.target.getBoundingClientRect();
            return aRect.top - bRect.top;
          });

        if (visibleEntries.length > 0) {
          setActiveId(visibleEntries[0].target.id);
        }
      },
      {
        // Root margin of "-100px 0px -66%" detects headings in upper viewport
        rootMargin: "-100px 0px -66%",
        threshold: 0,
      }
    );

    // Observe all h2, h3, h4 headings
    const headings = Array.from(
      document.querySelectorAll("#mainContent h2, #mainContent h3, #mainContent h4")
    );

    headings.forEach((heading) => observer.observe(heading));

    return () => {
      headings.forEach((heading) => observer.unobserve(heading));
      observer.disconnect();
    };
  }, []);

  return (
    <nav className="sticky top-16">
      {headings.map((heading) => (
        <a
          key={heading.id}
          href={`#${heading.id}`}
          className={cn(
            "block px-3 py-2 text-sm transition-colors",
            activeId === heading.id
              ? "border-l-2 border-primary-600 text-primary-600 font-semibold"
              : "text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900 border-l-2 border-transparent"
          )}
        >
          {heading.textContent}
        </a>
      ))}
    </nav>
  );
}
```

### Pattern B: getBoundingClientRect (Alternative for older browsers)
**From:** GitHub Docs, Google Cloud Platform

```typescript
function getActiveSection() {
  const headings = Array.from(
    document.querySelectorAll("h2, h3")
  ) as HTMLElement[];

  const visible = headings.filter((heading) => {
    const rect = heading.getBoundingClientRect();
    // Check if heading is in viewport
    return rect.top >= 0 && rect.top <= window.innerHeight / 2;
  });

  // Return first visible heading or topmost if none fully visible
  return visible[0] || headings[0];
}

// On scroll event
document.addEventListener("scroll", () => {
  const active = getActiveSection();
  updateActiveLink(active.id);
});
```

---

## 3. SMOOTH SCROLL TO SECTION PATTERNS

### Pattern A: Click Handler with Smooth Scroll
**From:** Supabase, Flowbite

```typescript
function handleTocLinkClick(e: React.MouseEvent<HTMLAnchorElement>) {
  e.preventDefault();

  const href = e.currentTarget.getAttribute("href");
  if (!href) return;

  const targetId = href.slice(1); // Remove #
  const target = document.getElementById(targetId);

  if (target) {
    // Smooth scroll with offset for sticky header
    const headerHeight = 80; // Height of sticky header
    const elementPosition = target.getBoundingClientRect().top + window.scrollY;
    const offsetPosition = elementPosition - headerHeight;

    window.scrollTo({
      top: offsetPosition,
      behavior: "smooth",
    });

    // Update URL without page jump
    window.history.pushState(null, "", `#${targetId}`);
  }
}
```

### Pattern B: Use Native HTML Scroll Behavior
```typescript
// In your TOC links
<a href={`#${headingId}`} className={styles.tocLink}>
  {headingText}
</a>

// CSS handles smooth scroll
html {
  scroll-behavior: smooth;
}
```

---

## 4. RESPONSIVE COLLAPSE ON MOBILE

### Pattern A: Sheet/Modal Drawer (Supabase)
```typescript
interface MobileTocProps {
  items: TocItem[];
}

export function MobileToc({ items }: MobileTocProps) {
  const [open, setOpen] = useState(false);

  // Close drawer when hash changes
  useEffect(() => {
    const handleHashChange = () => setOpen(false);
    window.addEventListener("hashchange", handleHashChange);
    return () => window.removeEventListener("hashchange", handleHashChange);
  }, []);

  return (
    <>
      {/* Mobile button */}
      <button 
        onClick={() => setOpen(true)}
        className="lg:hidden fixed bottom-6 right-6 z-40"
        aria-label="Open table of contents"
      >
        <MenuIcon />
      </button>

      {/* Sheet drawer */}
      <Sheet open={open} onOpenChange={setOpen}>
        <SheetContent side="right" className="w-64">
          <SheetHeader>
            <SheetTitle>On this page</SheetTitle>
          </SheetHeader>
          <nav className="space-y-2">
            {items.map((item) => (
              <a
                key={item.id}
                href={`#${item.id}`}
                className="block text-sm py-2 px-3 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded"
              >
                {item.title}
              </a>
            ))}
          </nav>
        </SheetContent>
      </Sheet>
    </>
  );
}
```

### Pattern B: Collapsible Details Element
```typescript
export function ResponsiveToc() {
  return (
    <>
